9.1 Xinerama
============

StumpWM will attempt to detect Xinerama heads at startup (and at no
other time.)  Heads are logically contained by screens.  In a
dual-monitor Xinerama configuration, there will be one screen with two
heads.  Non-rectangular layouts are supported (frames will not be
created in the ’dead zone’.)  And message windows will be displayed on
the current head–that is, the head to which the currently focused frame
belongs.


